article.description: Devin Cannady tied a career-high with 17 points and Spencer Weisz had 14 points and 10 rebounds to help Princeton beat Bucknell 89-77 on Tuesday night.
article.headline: Princeton uses big 1st half to beat Bucknell 89-77
article.linkText: Princeton uses big 1st half to beat Bucknell 89-77
article.story: PRINCETON, N.J. -- Devin Cannady tied a career-high with 17 points and Spencer Weisz had 14 points and 10 rebounds to help Princeton beat Bucknell 89-77 on Tuesday night. Cannady hit three of the Tigers' 10 3-pointers and Weisz made two. Henry Caruso and Steven Cook added 13 points apiece for Princeton (7-3), which has won four of the last five games in the series. Weisz recorded his second double-double of the season. After a back-and-fourth start, Princeton went on a 23-7 spurt and led 48-29 at halftime. The Tigers led by as many as 25 points. Both teams shot over 54 percent from the field overall but Princeton outrebounded Bucknell 41-22, including 12-2 on the offensive glass. Chris Hass led Bucknell (3-7) with 21 points and Zach Thomas added 16 points.
